<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-196-574  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 196 574.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  April 17 1989 v6 n15 p1(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NASA to launch new era with switching satellite. (includes relatedarticle on technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Herbst, Kris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>NASA will launch the Advanced Communications Technology Satellite(ACTS) in May 1992.andP;  The satellite will simultaneously distributemultiple T-1 circuits to 2.4-meter-diameter Ka-band earthstations.andP;  Designed to last for two years, ACTS will be used forexperimenting with advanced communications technologies which mayreplace cable and microwave links to remote areas.andP;  ACTStechnology is well-suited for a variety of applications, includingconsolidating various high-speed communications types, videonetworking, and emergency communications restoration.andP;  More than100 organizations have expressed an interest in experimenting withthe satellite network.andP;  ACTS is seen as one way of enabling the USto retain world leadership in connectivity technology, and as suchis supported by the Congress.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     NASASatellite CommunicationsHigh TechnologyConnectivityAdvanced Communications Technology Satellite (Artificialsatellite).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>